<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2011-02-22</DATELINE><TITLE>Reflections on pandemics, past and present</TITLE><BODY>The author reflects on her personal experiences during the 2009 H1N1 influenza, acquired immune deficiency syndrome (AIDS), and severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) pandemics. The roles played by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention related to pregnancy-associated influenza during the 2009 pandemic are described. Risk communication principles are summarized and resources provided.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>